    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="1027"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1027">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3456</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-17T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 18, 2.58 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3354. Esthonian delegation Stockholm received following telegram from their
                    government at Revel: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>German troops [evacuating] Walk about December 20 and it is expected that
                            Lettish Bolsheviks will then occupy Walk. Bolshevik <pb facs="0950"
                                n="860" xml:id="pg_860"/> bands now operating 20 miles south Dorpat.
                            Our troops evacuated Wesenberg and Bolsheviks advancing on wide front
                            along winter routes where difficult make stand with our small forces
                            against them. Convince Allied Ministers necessity of sending immediately
                            at least two infantry regiments with some artillery. Provisional
                            government places Esthonian republic, until definite decision at peace
                            conference, under protection Allies. Quick-Allied action will save
                            depots with goods worth millions.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Paris; copy to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MIN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
